added.title: Witches Brew
added.description: The Titans throw a Halloween party and invite the Justice League but the witches brew Robin creates has side effects.

added.title: Halloween vs. Christmas
added.description: When Santa tries to take over Halloween, it's up to the Titans and a few ghouls to stop him.

added.description: Batman and Commissioner Gordon check in on various happenings around Jump City.

added.title: TV Knight 2
added.description: Batman and Commissioner Gordon have a slumber party and watch their favorite TV shows.

added.description: Sick of losing the costume contest to the Hive Five every year, the Titans hatch a scheme to win.

added.description: The Titans' Halloween party is interupted by the Hive Five robbing a candy factory.

added.title: Halloween
added.description: Raven tries to put the spirit of Halloween back in Halloween.

added.title: Campfire Stories
added.description: The Titans are having a terrible time on their camping trip so Robin suggests that they each tell a scary campfire story.

added.title: Charlie's Halloween Thing 2
added.description: Charlie tells some scary stories featuring the Bears and their friends.

added.title: Charlie's Halloween Thing
added.description: Charlie hosts an evening of spooky stories starring the Bears.

added.title: Yard Sale
added.description: Each of the Bears get offbeat items at a local yard sale. Their new possessions send them on their own separate adventures.

added.title: Nom Nom's Entourage
added.description: Nom Nom recruits the Bears to act as his entourage of friends. But when the Bears realize Nom Nom doesn't understand friendship, they decide to kick their day of bonding into high gear.

added.title: Losing Ice
added.description: Feeling unappreciated, Ice Bear leaves his brothers to be the chef of a restaurant. Desperate to fill the void, Grizz and Panda look for Ice Bear's replacement.

added.title: Fashion Bears
added.description: In order to abide by the clothing policy of their favorite Boba shop, the Bears get some new outfits. But with new looks come new lives including office work, fashion modeling and even falling in love!

added.title: Chicken and Waffles
added.description: Panda needs to meet his brothers at the most exclusive restaurant in town. But when he loses his contacts lenses and can't see, Panda needs Charlie's help to get him into the city.

added.title: Nom Nom
added.description: When Nom Nom shows up on the Bears' doorstep, disheveled and deposed from his spot as cutest internet star ever after a recent meltdown, he enlists the Bears to help him regain his title.

added.title: Charlie
added.description: You know that one annoying friend who just can't get the hint? That's Charlie, and he's Bigfoot. The Bears meet him when Charlie signs up on a home-sharing website to spend a weekend with the Bears. Charlie is the worst possible house guest for the Bears and nearly destroys their house.

added.title: Charlie and the Snake
added.description: Charlie is a solo guy who, like the Bears, would love to find a place for himself in the world. In an effort to do so, Charlie throws a party, but ends up going on an adventure with the unlikeliest of animals, a wild snake.

added.title: Hibernation
added.description: The bears, being an urban bunch, hadn't ever heard of the idea of hibernation until Chloe tells them about it. Grizz, loving the idea of eating a ton and then just sleeping to his heart's content, goes for it with reckless abandon.  But Grizz is so excited for hibernating... that he can't fall asleep.

added.title: The Ghouls
added.description: It's Halloween in Elmore. As the kids go trick or treating we see what everyone in town is up to. The ghosts and ghouls are finding it increasingly difficult to scare children, and are only scaring part-time. Can Gumball and Darwin help them get their scare back?

added.title: The Scam
added.description: At Halloween show and tell, the class isn't buying Gumball's story about Gargaroth the Devourer until Carrie fakes a terrifying haunting. The kids convince the school to hire them as ghost exterminators and take their payment in Halloween candy. But when it turns out Gargaroth is real, suddenly Gumball is expected to be the town's savior.

added.title: The Slide
added.description: A chance encounter with the woman of his dreams inspires Rocky to stop living life online and find love with the help of the latest dating app. Gumball and Darwin try to help Rocky through the tricky world of online romance. In the race to find Rocky's dream girl, they discover people can forgive almost anything when you tell them you're acting in the name of love.

added.title: The Stars
added.description: When Dad gives Larry's hairdresser a bad review for saying he's bald, he gets offered a free haircut. This inspires Gumball and Darwin to go on a reviewing spree across town, forcing Larry to give them stuff with the threat of a bad review. Just because the customer is always right doesn't mean that what they're doing isn't wrong.

added.title: The Sorcerer
added.description: Gumball refuses to accept he is the only kid at school that doesn't have special powers. He convinces Mrs. Jotunheim, Hector's mom, to take him on as his apprentice but she soon learns leaving Gumball unsupervised around magic is a big mistake.

added.title: The Vacation
added.description: The Wattersons set off on a relaxing vacation and end up running for their lives! The Wattersons are swapping scary stories on a family vacation, when their car breaks down in the middle of the desert. They are left with no alternative but to trust a complete stranger, whose appearance matches the scary guy in Mom's story. When the stranger brings them to a derelict gas station, just as he did in mom's made-up scary story, the Wattersons can no longer pretend the story isn't coming true . . .

added.title: The Mirror
added.description: When Gumball refuses to forward a scare email, the curse becomes all too real. Gumball receives a scare email from a freaky ghost and decides to ignore it despite Darwin's advice. He refuses to admit it but the curse starts to come true and his whole family gets dragged into another dimension. Gumball and Darwin, with help from Carrie, set out to save their family.

added.title: The Flower
added.description: When Gumball sees Leslie with Penny, he is overcome with uncontrollable jealousy.

added.title: Halloween
added.description: Carrie takes Gumball, Darwin and Anais to a real haunted house party on Halloween!

added.title: The Skull
added.description: Gumball and Darwin make friends with classmate Clayton, a compulsive liar who can shape-change!

added.title: The Ghost
added.description: Gumball must learn to say "no" when Carrie the Ghost uses his body against his will.

added.title: The Poltergeist
added.description: Gumball and Darwin give Mr Robinson a home and end up saving his marriage.

added.title: The Curse
added.description: Gumball experiences an impossibly unfortunate chain of events.

added.title: Super-Villain Team-Up
added.description: After a lull in alien antics, a restless Ben suggests to Max and Gwen that he might be a better hero if he went solo, but once Vilgax enlists the help of Zombozo to build a giant hypno-mechanism to hypnotize the entire world, Ben must rethink his strategy if he is to defeat the super-villain team-up.

added.title: Innervasion Part 3: Strange Bedfellows
added.description: After the Junkbot shoots the Omnitrix and it begins glowing neon-blue, an imprisoned Vilgax explains it is now a gateway through which the Fulmini Empire will invade Earth, but the only way to stop them is from within the Omnitrix, so Ben must team up with the ultimate baddie if he is to save his planet.

added.title: Innervasion Part 4: Mind over Alien Matter
added.description: While inside the Omnitrix, Ben and Vilgax must work together if they are to close the gateway, but once the Fulmini leader, the High Override, appears, even that might not be enough. Luckily, help arrives in the form of a being calling itself Glitch!

added.title: Innervasion Part 2: Call the Dream Police
added.description: After defeating the Warbot and discovering Vilgax inside, Ben's "secret voices" only worsen and begin affecting his sleep, but once Gwen discovers a sleepwalking Ben using missing items from the campsite to create his own massive Junkbot, it is up to Ben to stop his own creation.

added.title: Innervasion Part 1: Message in a Boxcar
added.description: As Team Tennyson prepares their boxcar for an upcoming race, Ben is hearing voices and is unable to go Upgrade to enhance his car, but once the race is interrupted by a mysterious Warbot, Ben must overcome the voices inside his head if he is to defeat the giant adversary.

added.title: The Haunted Dollhouse
added.description: Craig and his friends find themselves being followed by a creepy doll and its haunted dollhouse.

added.title: Trick or Creek
added.description: It's Halloween at the Creek, and Craig is on a mission to collect as much candy as humanly possible, but a spooky ghoul from the Creek's past threatens his haul.

added.title: Creek Daycare
added.description: Craig and his sister, Jessica, try their hand at running the daycare at the Creek.

added.title: Sugar Smugglers
added.description: Craig, Kelsey and JP become smugglers to sneak candy to kids in need.

added.title: Sleepover at JP's
added.description: JP invites his friends over for a sleepover, but it happens to be on the night of a huge game of Flashlight Tag in the Creek!

added.title: Tea Timer's Ball
added.description: The Tea Timers throw a dance and invite everyone in the Creek. Craig believes it's solely to prank him, while Kelsey deals with an unwanted admirer.

added.title: The Cardboard Identity
added.description: Craig and his friends stumble upon a mysterious bunker made of cardboard beneath the Creek.

added.title: Ancients of the Creek
added.description: Craig, Kelsey and JP discover an ancient fort that belonged to the first kids in the Creek.

added.title: Mortimor to the Rescue
added.description: When Craig, Kelsey and JP get stranded in murky water, it's up to Mortimor to save the day!

added.title: Secret in a Bottle
added.description: Craig needs to get a secret off his chest, so he pays a visit to the Keeper of Secrets in the Creek.

added.title: Trading Day
added.description: After Craig accidentally destroys a shipment of rare Chocorolls at the Trading Tree, Kit makes him work off his debt by running her trades throughout the Creek!

added.title: Sunday Clothes
added.description: JP dirties his last clean clothes and he must wear his Sunday best to the creek.

added.title: Escape from Family Dinner
added.description: There's a huge water balloon fight at the creek but Craig is stuck at home for a family dinner, unless he can escape.

added.title: Monster in the Garden
added.description: Craig is determined to catch the monster that has been wreaking havoc in Granddad's garden.

added.title: Duncan Carving
added.description: Duncan takes advantage of a questionable Halloween legend to steal candy from his classmates.

added.title: Ghoul Spirit
added.description: Gwen rejects the friendship of a friendly ghost.

added.title: Weiner Takes All
added.description: After forgetting to book a Hot Diggity Doggity Dog mascot on National Hotdog Day, Chef tries to pass off an Australian man dressed as a kangaroo as a substitute.

added.title: Apoca-lice Now
added.description: When Chef brokers a truce with lice by selecting three kids to "host" them on their heads, Courtney instigates a kid vs. lice war.

added.description: An entire episode chronicles the ninja's most bizarre adventure yet: in which Cole, Princess Vania and Master Wu fall down a seemingly endless tunnel, into the bowels of Shintaro Mountain.

added.title: Questing For Quests

added.title: A Rocky Start
added.description: The ninja have found their quest! Now they just have to get there, which involves a road trip through the Desert of Doom, a region supposedly inhabited by a giant scarab beetle.

added.title: The Belly of the Beast
added.description: To repair the Land-Bounty, the ninja must retrieve a critical engine component that has been swallowed by a giant scarab beetle.

added.title: Booby-Traps, and How To Survive Them
added.description: The ninja team up with a reluctant Clutch Powers to enter a mysterious pyramid where they inadvertently unleash an ancient evil.

added.title: The Kaiju Protocol
added.description: Back in Ninjago City, Wu and Pixal attempt to locate the Never-Realm, and accidentally unleash a dreaded creature from the Departed Realm…

added.title: Corruption

added.title: A Fragile Hope

added.title: Once and for All
added.description: Nya, Jay, Cole and Kai face off against the Ice Emperor's dreaded dragon, while Lloyd and his newfound allies, Kataru and Grimfax, confront the Ice Emperor himself.

added.title: Awakenings
added.description: The dramatic conclusion of the Never-Realm saga, in which old friends are reunited and the power of friendship is pitted against the corrupting power of the Scroll of Forbidden Spinjitzu.

added.description: In order to prove their bravery, V&V head to a haunted island to retrieve a special doll, but Charlene and Pineapple are intent on getting it first.

added.description: Victor sets up a haunted corn maze, but the town kids think it's lame. Vic decides to make the maze scarier by enlisting the help of El Silbon (The Whistler) to really scare the kids, but El Silbon has plans of his own.

added.title: Lonely Haunts Club
added.description: Instead of celebrating Valentine's Day, Vic & Val take on a dare to explore a haunted mansion with their rivals, Charlene & Pineapple.

added.title: Lonely Haunts Club 3: La Llorona
added.description: When Val sets out to get a little privacy in the woods, Vic is bent on pranking his unsuspecting brother,  that is, until Val goes missing.

added.title: Escaramuza
added.description: When Val's favorite Escaramuza team loses a member, he convinces Xochi to join the squad. He becomes her coach and will do anything to win the big competition.

added.description: When Vic joins a group of nighttime skaters called Los Perdidos, Val becomes suspicious of Vic's strange, new, vampire-like behavior.

added.description: Vultureman has got a brand new invention but there's one big problem: he stole the idea from Panthro! Oh, also Vultureman is using his invention to take over Third Earth. So, there are two big problems.

added.title: Warrior Maiden Invasion
added.description: Third Earth is being overrun by super tough, super buff Warrior Maidens and it looks like the ThunderCats are next on their hit list! It's gonna be up to the ThunderKittens to save the day even though the kittens are so small and the Warrior Maidens are so big.

added.title: Horror Club
added.description: Steven goes to the lighthouse to watch scary movies with Ronaldo, Lars and Sadie.

added.title: Stuck Together
added.description: Steven and Lars spend some time together.

added.title: Off Colors
added.description: Steven finds some unusual new allies.

added.title: Dewey Wins

added.title: Jungle Moon
added.description: Stevonnie finds themself alone on an adventure.

added.title: The Kindergarten Kid

added.title: Buddy's Book
added.description: Steven and Connie take a trip to the library and discover a long forgotten book.

added.title: Future Boy Zoltron
added.description: Steven fills in for a fortune teller at Funland.

added.description: Steven learns about Onion's secret group of friends.

added.title: Three Gems and a Baby
added.description: Greg tells Steven the story of his first winter with Steven.

added.description: Steven and the Gems take off on a search and recovery mission.

added.title: Steven's Birthday
added.description: Steven has a birthday party out at the barn, and decides he has some growing up to do.
